# NanthAI Edge — Environment Variables
# =====================================
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
#
# This file documents ALL environment variables needed to run NanthAI Edge.
# Variables are split between:
#   1. This file (.env.local) — used by the Convex CLI
#   2. web/.env.local — used by the Vite web frontend
#   3. Convex environment variables — set via `npx convex env set KEY VALUE`
#
# See the self-hosting guide in README.md for setup instructions.

# ==============================================================================
# Convex CLI Configuration (this file)
# ==============================================================================

# Your Convex deployment name (from `npx convex dev`)
CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=dev:your-deployment-name

# Your Convex deployment URL
CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud

# Your Convex site URL (for HTTP endpoints)
CONVEX_SITE_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.site

# Clerk JWT issuer domain (your Clerk instance)
CLERK_JWT_ISSUER_DOMAIN=https://your-instance.clerk.accounts.dev

# ==============================================================================
# Convex Backend Environment Variables
# ==============================================================================
# Set these via: npx convex env set KEY VALUE
#
# Required vs Optional:
#   [REQUIRED]  — the app won't function without this
#   [OPTIONAL]  — feature-specific, app works without it
#   [AUTO]      — set automatically by the Convex platform

# ── Authentication ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [REQUIRED] Clerk JWT issuer domain (same as above, also needed as Convex env var)
# npx convex env set CLERK_JWT_ISSUER_DOMAIN https://your-instance.clerk.accounts.dev

# ── AI Models ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE: There is no server-side OpenRouter API key. Every user brings their
# own OpenRouter key via PKCE OAuth. The key is stored per-user in the
# userSecrets table and used for all AI operations (chat, search, memory,
# scheduled jobs, subagents, etc.). You do NOT need to provide an OpenRouter
# key as an env var.

# [OPTIONAL] Artificial Analysis API key for model benchmark data sync.
# Enriches the model catalog with benchmark scores (intelligence, coding, speed).
# If not set, benchmark sync is silently skipped — the app works fine without it.
# npx convex env set ARTIFICIAL_ANALYSIS_API_KEY aa_your-key-here

# ── Payments (Stripe) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [OPTIONAL] All four are required together if you want to gate features behind a paid Pro tier.
# npx convex env set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY your-stripe-secret-key
# npx convex env set STRIPE_PRICE_ID price_your-price-id
# npx convex env set STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET your-webhook-secret
# npx convex env set WEB_APP_URL https://your-domain.com

# ── Google Integration (OAuth) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# [OPTIONAL] Required for Google Calendar/Drive/Contacts integration.
# npx convex env set GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
# npx convex env set GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID your-google-web-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
# npx convex env set GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_SECRET your-google-client-secret

# ── Microsoft Integration (OAuth) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# [OPTIONAL] Required for Microsoft Calendar/OneDrive/Outlook integration.
# npx convex env set MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID your-microsoft-app-id
# npx convex env set MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET your-microsoft-client-secret

# ── Notion Integration (OAuth) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# [OPTIONAL] Required for Notion integration.
# npx convex env set NOTION_CLIENT_ID your-notion-client-id
# npx convex env set NOTION_CLIENT_SECRET your-notion-client-secret

# ── Push Notifications — Web (VAPID) ───────────────────────────────────────
# [OPTIONAL] Required for web push notifications.
# Generate VAPID keys with: npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
# npx convex env set WEB_PUSH_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY your-vapid-public-key
# npx convex env set WEB_PUSH_VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY your-vapid-private-key
# npx convex env set WEB_PUSH_VAPID_SUBJECT mailto:your-email@example.com
